               <p>FRANCIS BEDFORD. I <rs id="t18250915-137-viclabel744" type="occupation">keep a clothes' shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-137-victim756 t18250915-137-viclabel744"></join> in <placeName id="t18250915-137-crimeloc745">Finsbury-market</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-137-crimeloc745" type="placeName" value="Finsbury-market"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-137-crimeloc745" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-137-off742 t18250915-137-crimeloc745"></join>. I was outside my shop about half-past one o'clock on the 20th of July: the prisoner came, and while she was there I saw her put her hand to the window, and take something, which she put into her bosom - as she was coming out I took hold of her, and said "Where is the handkerchief you took last night?" she said "I took none;" I then said "What have you taken now?" I turned her shawl aside, and saw a corner of this handkerchief out of her bosom.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-137-person757">
                  ANN 
                  BEDFORD
               <interp inst="t18250915-137-person757" type="surname" value="BEDFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-137-person757" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-137-person757" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prosecutor's wife. I served the prisoner at our shop on the 20th of July - I did not<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182509150056"></xptr>see her take any thing, but I saw my husband take this handkerchief from her at the door.</p>
